Dany Mukesha

Bio

Hi!

I am Dany, Member of Computational Biology Team at Firalis in Huningue since 2023. I am currently pursuing a Phd program funded by Marie Skodowska-Curie Actions at The University of Cte dAzur in Nice, France.

My Research consists in identifying and validating body fluid biomarkers for the diagnosis of early-onset Alzheimers disease.

Experience

Catenate Group | Back-End/Tibco Developer | 2021 - 2023

Wayne State University | Bioinformatics Analyst | 2022 - 2023

Manchester University | Research Assistant | 2020 - 2021

Gemelli Hospital | Scientific Collaborator (Bioinformatics) | 2020

Education

The University of Cte dAzur | Nice, France

Ph.D.in Bioinformatics | 2023 - 2025

The University of Tor Vergata | Rome, Italy

M.Sc. in Bioinformatics | 2020 - 2023

The University of Sapienza | Rome, Italy

B.S. in Bioinformatics | 2016 - 2019
